WEBVTT

00:00.894 --> 00:03.731
<i>353,015.</i>

00:04.326 --> 00:06.977
<i>That's how many babies</i>
<i>will be born today.</i>

00:07.029 --> 00:10.147
<i>It seems weird to me that</i>
<i>they weren't here yesterday...</i>

00:10.199 --> 00:11.916
<i>That they didn't have</i>
<i>their parents</i>

00:11.983 --> 00:13.484
<i>and their parents</i>
<i>didn't have them...</i>

00:13.535 --> 00:16.954
<i>That this is</i>
<i>their first day ever.</i>

00:17.005 --> 00:19.707
<i>353,015.</i>

00:21.877 --> 00:23.010
Hey, buddy.

00:23.095 --> 00:25.179
How you holding up?

00:25.264 --> 00:27.131
Fine.

00:27.182 --> 00:28.132
How's mom?

00:28.183 --> 00:29.500
She's good.

00:29.551 --> 00:31.302
She's being prepped, and
they're getting her her room,

00:31.353 --> 00:34.405
and pretty soon,
you'll have a baby sister.

00:34.473 --> 00:36.974
How long does that take,
dad?

00:37.025 --> 00:38.226
That's hard to say.

00:38.310 --> 00:39.610
But I'll be with her.

00:39.678 --> 00:41.612
You're gonna hang out with Clay
and Aunt Quinn, okay?

00:41.680 --> 00:43.848
Okay.
I want to stay, though.

00:43.899 --> 00:45.733
I don't want to go home
until mom's okay,

00:45.818 --> 00:46.851
and Lydia, too.

00:46.902 --> 00:47.902
You sure?

00:47.970 --> 00:48.953
Could be all night.

00:49.020 --> 00:50.488
That's fine.

00:50.539 --> 00:52.189
I feel pretty strongly
about it.

00:52.241 --> 00:54.242
All right.

00:54.326 --> 00:56.026
Well, then,
I have respect that.

00:56.078 --> 00:58.329
You, my man,
are not a baby anymore.

00:58.380 --> 00:59.797
Nope.

00:59.865 --> 01:01.199
But <i>they</i> are.

01:03.702 --> 01:07.872
♪ Looking for reasons,
find that I'm... ♪

01:07.923 --> 01:12.193
Dad, do you remember
when I was born?

01:12.261 --> 01:15.396
Yeah.
I sure do.

01:15.481 --> 01:17.181
It's a boy.

01:17.232 --> 01:19.550
You're a dad!

01:19.601 --> 01:21.269
You did so good.

01:21.336 --> 01:23.554
We have a son.

01:23.622 --> 01:25.940
We have a son.
Here he is.

01:29.695 --> 01:34.449
Welcome to the world,
James Lucas Scott.

01:34.533 --> 01:35.900
Oh.

01:35.951 --> 01:39.353
He's so beautiful.

01:39.421 --> 01:43.841
♪ And I'll be waiting, waiting ♪

01:43.909 --> 01:48.412
♪ waiting, waiting,
waiting up ♪

01:48.464 --> 01:49.380
Hi.

01:49.431 --> 01:50.848
We're having a baby.

01:50.916 --> 01:53.584
Honey, you do understand
it takes about nine months.

01:53.635 --> 01:54.602
Of course.
What we meant to say is --

01:54.636 --> 01:55.770
we're adopting a baby,

01:55.854 --> 01:57.755
and the girl who's having it
is having it.

01:57.806 --> 01:58.756
Yeah.
Here.

01:58.807 --> 01:59.974
Now.
Somewhere.

02:00.058 --> 02:01.976
Okay. Well, first of all,
congratulations.

02:02.060 --> 02:04.025
And give me a second, and I'll find
you that room for you, okay?

02:04.314 --> 02:05.481
Thank you.

02:11.286 --> 02:13.538
Hi.
There's my guy.

02:13.605 --> 02:14.906
Ooh.

02:14.957 --> 02:16.290
You ready to be
a Big Brother?

02:16.375 --> 02:17.408
Yeah.

02:17.459 --> 02:18.960
How come
you're not in a bed?

02:19.044 --> 02:20.628
Well, this is the room
where they have me wait

02:20.712 --> 02:22.547
till I'm a little closer
to having the baby.

02:22.614 --> 02:24.165
So, is everything
all right?

02:24.249 --> 02:25.282
You feeling okay?

02:25.334 --> 02:27.251
Yeah. I feel great.
Thanks.

02:27.336 --> 02:29.587
Oh, I can't believe you're gonna
have a little sister.

02:29.638 --> 02:31.672
She's gonna need you
to watch out for her

02:31.757 --> 02:33.424
and protect her.

02:33.475 --> 02:35.343
Do you know that
by the time she's your age,

02:35.427 --> 02:36.744
you're gonna be
in high school?

02:36.812 --> 02:39.647
And when you and dad were
in high school, you had me.

02:39.731 --> 02:41.632
That's right.

02:42.968 --> 02:43.968
You're not allowed
to do that.

02:46.021 --> 02:48.806
Oh, I remember the night
I told your dad

02:48.857 --> 02:50.107
you were gonna be you.

02:50.158 --> 02:53.027
He was gonna have a son.

02:53.111 --> 02:54.412
Remember that, dad?

02:54.479 --> 02:55.913
Yeah.

02:55.981 --> 02:57.999
I had six turnovers
at the time.

02:58.083 --> 03:00.668
You're not allowed
to do that either.

03:00.752 --> 03:03.988
Six turnovers?

03:04.039 --> 03:07.258
That is not the Nathan Scott
I know.

03:07.325 --> 03:09.159
I got worried
when I didn't see you.

03:09.211 --> 03:11.829
It's okay.
Everything's fine.

03:15.300 --> 03:18.853
♪ But after all the dust
has settled ♪

03:18.937 --> 03:21.522
I need to ask you
a question.

03:21.590 --> 03:22.506
Mm-hmm.

03:22.558 --> 03:25.226
If I don't go to Duke...

03:25.310 --> 03:27.695
If I don't play
college basketball...

03:27.779 --> 03:31.849
I mean, if today is the best
it ever gets for me,

03:31.900 --> 03:33.901
will that be enough?

03:33.986 --> 03:36.821
Of course.

03:36.872 --> 03:39.240
Nathan, as long
as you're a good husband

03:39.324 --> 03:43.077
and a good father
to your son.

03:43.161 --> 03:45.379
What?

03:45.464 --> 03:47.048
It's a boy, Nathan.

03:48.634 --> 03:49.800
You're gonna have a son.

03:52.037 --> 03:55.139
♪ Either way ♪

03:55.206 --> 03:57.141
♪ either way ♪

03:57.208 --> 03:59.143
Hi.
Chloe, hi.

03:59.210 --> 04:00.344
Hi.

04:00.395 --> 04:01.262
I told you
it was coming sooner

04:01.346 --> 04:02.730
than we thought.

04:02.814 --> 04:03.881
Wow. I guess so.

04:03.932 --> 04:05.516
How are you feeling?

04:05.567 --> 04:06.901
What can we do?
Can we get you anything?

04:06.985 --> 04:08.819
Call your parents --
No. No.

04:08.887 --> 04:10.771
No, thanks.
I'll -- I'll be fine.

04:10.856 --> 04:12.023
Okay.

04:12.074 --> 04:13.774
Well, we just want you to know
we're here.

04:13.859 --> 04:16.127
And we're gonna be here.
We're not going anywhere.

04:16.194 --> 04:17.894
Okay.
Okay.

04:17.946 --> 04:20.447
Maybe you guys can come check up
on me a little later.

04:20.531 --> 04:22.733
Yeah. Of course.
Whenever you need us.

04:24.953 --> 04:29.040
You're gonna do great.

04:29.091 --> 04:30.424
♪ Right away ♪

04:30.509 --> 04:31.592
Okay.

04:31.677 --> 04:34.845
All right.
See you.

04:34.913 --> 04:40.768
♪ Running back to you ♪

04:40.852 --> 04:43.688
Hey.

04:43.755 --> 04:44.755
Yo.
Check it out, dude.

04:44.806 --> 04:46.256
I got us
all kinds of stuff.

04:46.308 --> 04:48.275
We have DVDs, snacks.

04:48.360 --> 04:49.276
Comic books.

04:49.361 --> 04:50.778
Graphic novels.

04:50.862 --> 04:52.763
Oh, my gosh, UNO.
I'm the UNO king.

04:52.814 --> 04:54.065
Okay,
that's a game of luck.

04:54.116 --> 04:56.033
There is just zero skill to it
whatsoever.

04:56.101 --> 04:57.284
Said not the king.

04:57.369 --> 04:59.570
That sentence
had zero sense to it.

04:59.621 --> 05:02.106
Anyway, what do you want
to do first, Jame?

05:02.157 --> 05:04.726
I'm thinking I want to make
a book for Lydia...

05:04.739 --> 05:06.823
With pictures and stories
and stuff.

05:06.908 --> 05:08.308
Like a scrapbook?

05:08.359 --> 05:11.144
Yeah, but more like a book
that she can read someday

05:11.196 --> 05:12.996
and know all about stuff
that I didn't --

05:13.081 --> 05:16.700
stuff about mom, you guys,
and all our friends.

05:16.784 --> 05:17.918
Like, for example,
how Auntie Quinn

05:17.985 --> 05:19.319
is the master
of a game of chance.

05:19.370 --> 05:21.154
Or how Clay
is jealous about it.

05:21.206 --> 05:24.007
I think
it's a great idea, Jamie.

05:24.092 --> 05:25.492
Hey, you guys.
I was just about to call.

05:25.543 --> 05:26.927
Hales just checked in.

05:26.994 --> 05:28.178
Well, actually --
We heard.

05:28.263 --> 05:29.663
It's so exciting.

05:29.714 --> 05:30.847
Who needs snacks?

05:30.965 --> 05:32.182
Mm.
I think we're good.

05:32.267 --> 05:34.384
We have candy, gummy stuff,
candy cigars.

05:34.469 --> 05:36.520
We've also apparently mastered
the game of UNO.

05:36.604 --> 05:37.521
Really?

05:37.605 --> 05:39.273
Letting it go.

05:39.340 --> 05:40.857
What was that
all about?

05:40.942 --> 05:44.278
I just don't want to steal
Haley's thunder today.

05:44.345 --> 05:46.029
Especially for Jamie.

05:46.114 --> 05:48.014
If we have news first,
then we can tell them, okay?

05:48.066 --> 05:50.183
That's very sweet of you,
baby.

05:50.235 --> 05:51.451
But are we
really getting snacks?

05:51.519 --> 05:52.953
Because I was
kind of excited

05:53.020 --> 05:54.071
about that part, too.

05:54.155 --> 05:56.790
Yes,
we will get you snacks.

05:56.857 --> 05:57.908
Are you nervous?

05:57.992 --> 05:59.859
A little.

05:59.911 --> 06:00.911
Are you?

06:00.995 --> 06:01.995
No.

06:02.046 --> 06:04.047
More like
completely panicked.

06:04.132 --> 06:06.216
Oh.

06:08.703 --> 06:10.003
How you doing, baby?

06:10.054 --> 06:12.539
I'm a little panicked.
Can you tell me a story?

06:12.590 --> 06:14.057
Uh, story.

06:14.142 --> 06:15.058
Got it.

06:15.143 --> 06:16.176
What kind of story?

06:16.227 --> 06:18.228
Just a story.
Any story.

06:18.313 --> 06:19.646
All right, all right.
Um...

06:19.714 --> 06:21.515
I-I-I-I got nothing.
Oh!

06:21.566 --> 06:23.817
In the history of the world,
any story that's ever been told.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.986
Okay, I'm sorry. All I can
think of is the Three Little Pigs.

06:26.053 --> 06:27.887
I don't know why the
Three Little Pigs. I have no idea.

06:27.939 --> 06:29.072
But it's --

06:29.157 --> 06:30.524
A memory, then.

06:30.575 --> 06:32.058
Just something
to distract me, please.

06:32.110 --> 06:33.994
Okay, okay. How about this?
How about this?

06:34.061 --> 06:36.830
Did I ever tell you
about the high-school clown --

06:36.897 --> 06:38.415
Don't say "clown."

06:38.499 --> 06:39.950
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Jerk. The high-school jerk

06:40.034 --> 06:43.754
who fell for the beautiful,
sarcastic girl who hated clowns?

06:43.838 --> 06:46.957
I like that story.
Tell me that story.

06:47.041 --> 06:47.958
Okay. Okay.

06:48.042 --> 06:50.844
Um, she was tutoring him.

06:50.911 --> 06:52.512
But they both knew
it was something more,

06:52.580 --> 06:55.248
and so one day, when
he had screwed up yet again...

06:57.000 --> 07:03.074
Learn the unknown English words
of this movie at www.skeebdo.com

07:06.277 --> 07:07.978
You trying to wake up
my parents?

07:08.062 --> 07:10.230
That's their room.

07:10.281 --> 07:11.765
Wait. Haley.

07:11.816 --> 07:14.151
Look, I need to apologize,
okay?

07:14.235 --> 07:15.769
You should buy them in bulk

07:15.820 --> 07:17.454
if you're gonna hand apologies
out that often.

07:17.538 --> 07:19.239
Look, will you just --

07:19.290 --> 07:22.209
I don't know how to do this,
all right?

07:22.276 --> 07:23.610
I'm --
I'm not like you.

07:23.661 --> 07:24.995
What does that mean?

07:25.079 --> 07:28.582
All right, I screw up a lot.
All right?

07:28.633 --> 07:30.334
And being around you,

07:30.418 --> 07:32.302
I just don't want to be
that guy anymore.

07:32.387 --> 07:34.004
Who do you want to be,
Nathan?

07:34.088 --> 07:36.923
I want to be somebody who's good
enough to be seen with you.

07:36.974 --> 07:39.643
You should have thought of that
last night.

07:39.727 --> 07:40.927
You know, I keep
putting myself out there.

07:40.978 --> 07:42.796
And you keep blowing it.

07:42.847 --> 07:44.648
And it's probably a good thing
because at this point

07:44.732 --> 07:46.600
there's nothing that
you can say or do that's
gonna surprise me.

07:46.651 --> 07:54.307
♪ Everybody's watching you now ♪

07:54.359 --> 07:55.826
Except that.

07:55.910 --> 07:59.079
♪ Everybody waits for you now ♪

07:59.147 --> 08:01.481
You shouldn't have done that,
Nathan.

08:01.532 --> 08:04.951
But I wanted to.

08:05.002 --> 08:07.821
Yeah.

08:07.872 --> 08:11.958
♪ I dare you to move ♪

08:12.009 --> 08:15.429
♪ I dare you to move ♪

08:15.496 --> 08:18.999
And they fell in love.

08:19.067 --> 08:20.467
And they had a son.

08:20.518 --> 08:21.601
And soon...

08:21.669 --> 08:23.103
They'll have
a daughter.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.971
Mm-hmm.

08:25.022 --> 08:27.574
And they'll all live
happily ever after.

08:27.642 --> 08:28.708
I promise.

08:28.776 --> 08:32.479
♪ Like today never happened ♪

08:32.530 --> 08:39.785
♪ today never happened before ♪

08:46.127 --> 08:48.829
♪ I don't have to be anyone
other ♪

08:48.880 --> 08:51.364
♪ than the birth of two souls
in one ♪

08:51.416 --> 08:54.134
♪ part of where I'm going ♪

08:54.201 --> 08:57.421
♪ is knowing
where I'm coming from ♪

08:57.505 --> 08:59.923
♪ I don't want to be anything ♪

09:00.007 --> 09:03.376
♪ other than what I've been
trying to be lately ♪

09:03.428 --> 09:06.263
♪ all I have to do
is think of me ♪

09:06.347 --> 09:09.266
♪ and I have peace of mind ♪

09:09.350 --> 09:11.551
♪ I'm tired
of looking 'round rooms ♪

09:11.602 --> 09:13.019
♪ wondering what I gotta do ♪

09:13.070 --> 09:14.821
♪ or who I'm supposed to be ♪

09:14.889 --> 09:17.824
♪ I don't want to be anything ♪

09:17.892 --> 09:20.076
♪ other than me ♪

09:20.101 --> 09:23.101
<font color=00fff00>♪ One Tree Hill 8x18♪</font>
