09:23.102 --> 09:25.602
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00ff00>elderman</font> ==

09:36.500 --> 09:39.602
<i>14,709.</i>

09:39.669 --> 09:42.788
<i>That's how many babies</i>
<i>are born in an hour.</i>

09:42.856 --> 09:47.593
<i>That's 245 new lives</i>
<i>every minute of every day.</i>

09:48.671 --> 09:52.307
<i>By the way,</i>
<i>since I've been standing here,</i>

09:52.375 --> 09:54.610
<i>another hundred babies</i>
<i>were born.</i>

09:54.677 --> 09:58.564
<i>But none of them were my mom's.</i>

09:58.642 --> 10:00.592
Hey, buddy.
What are you doing?

10:00.644 --> 10:03.279
Making a learner's manual
for Lydia.

10:03.363 --> 10:06.198
Clay says you can't tell
the players without a program.

10:06.266 --> 10:07.933
That's cool.
Am I in it?

10:07.984 --> 10:09.068
Yep.

10:09.119 --> 10:11.570
I just need
a little information.

10:11.621 --> 10:12.938
Okay.
Ask me anything.

10:12.989 --> 10:14.907
Okay.

10:14.958 --> 10:17.827
When was the first time
you met my mom?

10:17.894 --> 10:21.080
Isn't there anything else
you'd like to know?

10:21.131 --> 10:22.832
It's kind of important.

10:22.916 --> 10:24.717
Well...

10:24.784 --> 10:28.420
It's kind of
a funny story.

10:28.471 --> 10:31.090
So, we should
totally hang out more often.

10:31.141 --> 10:32.224
What is your name,
anyway?

10:32.292 --> 10:33.342
Haley.

10:33.426 --> 10:35.511
Oh, no.
See, I don't like that name.

10:35.595 --> 10:37.963
Let's call you Brooke.

10:38.031 --> 10:39.181
I don't get it.

10:39.266 --> 10:41.851
How come
you were acting so weird?

10:41.935 --> 10:42.935
Were you sick?

10:42.986 --> 10:46.238
Yes. Kind of sick.
Yes.

10:48.325 --> 10:51.527
Look who it is --
Clay and Quinn.

10:51.611 --> 10:53.195
What's up, guys?

10:53.280 --> 10:54.313
Hey-o.

10:55.699 --> 10:57.533
Did you guys know
that it's impossible

10:57.601 --> 10:58.784
to eat six crackers
in a minute?

10:58.835 --> 11:01.320
Random,
but perfectly timed.

11:01.371 --> 11:02.821
That doesn't sound
impossible.

11:02.873 --> 11:04.089
That's what I said,
but we're gonna do it.

11:04.157 --> 11:05.291
You in?

11:05.342 --> 11:06.992
Okay.
Aunt Brooke, can you time us?

11:07.043 --> 11:08.377
Yeah.

11:08.461 --> 11:11.714
All right, team.
Six crackers, one minute.

11:11.798 --> 11:13.198
Ready? Set?

11:13.266 --> 11:14.099
Go.

11:20.607 --> 11:21.840
Oh, my gosh.
This is hard.

11:25.011 --> 11:26.445
30 seconds.

11:26.512 --> 11:28.447
I can't breathe.

11:28.514 --> 11:30.032
It's not so easy, is it?

11:31.851 --> 11:33.319
My mouth is all pasty.

11:33.370 --> 11:35.371
Come on. 20 seconds.
Keep going.

11:44.831 --> 11:46.465
And...Time.

11:46.532 --> 11:48.200
Mm.

11:48.251 --> 11:50.052
I was so close.

11:50.136 --> 11:51.837
I wasn't close at all.

11:51.888 --> 11:53.756
I think I'm gonna be sick.
Mm-hmm.

11:55.091 --> 11:56.976
We should make Julian
try this.

11:57.043 --> 11:57.977
Where is Julian?

11:59.813 --> 12:01.680
Julian!

12:20.116 --> 12:21.566
They're beautiful.

12:21.618 --> 12:23.402
So are you.

12:23.453 --> 12:25.087
♪ We've seen
what we never should ♪

12:25.155 --> 12:27.539
How you doing?

12:27.590 --> 12:30.542
Not so good.

12:30.593 --> 12:32.094
Yeah, I know.

12:32.178 --> 12:36.765
I don't think you do.

12:36.850 --> 12:40.019
No, I suppose I don't.

12:40.086 --> 12:42.304
But I want you
to know something.

12:42.372 --> 12:45.341
I know that I've talked about
slowing down

12:45.408 --> 12:48.444
and taking our time,
but I want you to know

12:48.528 --> 12:52.031
that whenever
we do get pregnant,

12:52.098 --> 12:55.985
that's gonna be
a great day.

12:56.069 --> 12:58.821
And I'll be more than okay
with it.

12:58.905 --> 13:01.740
♪ Planes crashing
and burn around us ♪

13:01.791 --> 13:03.542
We're not gonna have
that day.

13:03.609 --> 13:05.911
Baby, we will.

13:05.962 --> 13:09.281
No, we won't.

13:09.332 --> 13:12.418
♪ Three shouts,
and thank God I found you ♪

13:12.469 --> 13:14.670
♪ with the crowd
and the fog around you ♪

13:14.754 --> 13:17.840
They didn't
just tell me that...

13:17.924 --> 13:20.676
That I wasn't pregnant.

13:20.793 --> 13:24.229
They said
I'm never gonna be.

13:24.297 --> 13:26.448
I can't.

13:26.516 --> 13:30.069
You can't have children?
They told you that.

13:30.136 --> 13:32.154
I'm sorry.

13:32.238 --> 13:33.605
Brooke...

13:33.656 --> 13:39.862
♪ But I hope
it will get better ♪

13:39.946 --> 13:42.498
♪ these times
we're in together ♪

13:42.582 --> 13:44.533
Shh.

13:44.617 --> 13:46.485
Hey, shh, baby.
It's okay.

13:46.536 --> 13:49.004
It's not.

13:49.089 --> 13:50.339
It's going to be.

13:50.423 --> 13:52.491
I love you so much.

13:52.542 --> 13:54.043
But I want to have babies
with you.

13:54.127 --> 13:55.794
I want to have a family.

13:55.845 --> 13:57.212
Then we'll get
a second opinion.

13:57.297 --> 13:59.381
And a third, okay?

13:59.466 --> 14:00.933
We'll find the best doctors
out there.

14:01.000 --> 14:03.018
But what if --
Hey, shh, shh.

14:03.103 --> 14:06.004
I love you.

14:06.056 --> 14:08.307
That's all that matters.
I love you.

14:08.358 --> 14:10.476
♪ ...With ourselves ♪

14:10.527 --> 14:11.843
I love you, too.

14:11.895 --> 14:16.949
♪ Oh, heaven, can you hear us? ♪

14:17.016 --> 14:21.186
♪ right now we are not sure ♪

14:21.237 --> 14:23.021
Hey.

14:23.073 --> 14:25.574
♪ But I hope
it will get better ♪

14:25.625 --> 14:27.876
I love you.
You know that?

14:27.961 --> 14:30.862
And you're gonna be
an amazing mom...

14:30.914 --> 14:33.298
Tonight.

14:33.366 --> 14:36.135
I can barely breathe
when you say that.

14:36.202 --> 14:39.555
It's okay, baby.

14:39.639 --> 14:42.057
I'm here...
For all of it.

14:44.677 --> 14:48.514
Mm.

14:56.319 --> 14:59.237
<i>I think it's cool how people</i>
<i>celebrate the day you're born.</i>

14:59.288 --> 15:01.790
<i>Like, for the rest</i>
<i>of your life,</i>

15:01.874 --> 15:03.658
<i>they have cake and presents,</i>

15:03.743 --> 15:05.494
<i>and they celebrate</i>
<i>that you're here.</i>

15:05.578 --> 15:09.464
<i>There's something really nice</i>
<i>about that...</i>

15:09.549 --> 15:12.918
<i>Even when your Aunt Quinn</i>
<i>stuffs your face in the cake.</i>

15:12.969 --> 15:15.887
Aunt Quinn, you ate my cake
before I made a wish.

15:15.955 --> 15:16.888
Nah.

15:16.956 --> 15:18.757
See...

15:18.808 --> 15:20.392
I don't think
this is your <i>real</i> cake.

15:20.459 --> 15:23.728
If you look really, really
close, you can tell,

15:23.796 --> 15:27.349
because if it was,
I wouldn't be able to do this!

15:28.267 --> 15:30.685
Aah!

15:30.770 --> 15:33.321
You're so dead.

15:37.476 --> 15:40.478
♪ I'll give you everything
I got inside ♪

15:40.530 --> 15:42.080
Hey, remember
when you stuffed my face

15:42.147 --> 15:43.164
in my birthday cake?

15:44.483 --> 15:46.668
And then you, me, and mom
had that cake fight?

15:46.752 --> 15:47.919
That was awesome.

15:47.987 --> 15:50.205
It was, huh?

15:50.289 --> 15:51.756
Oh!

15:51.824 --> 15:54.042
Yes, it was.

15:54.126 --> 15:55.827
You know, pretty soon

15:55.878 --> 15:56.928
you're gonna have
"remember whens"

15:56.996 --> 15:57.762
with
your little sister.

15:59.849 --> 16:01.233
Are you excited
to meet her?

16:01.300 --> 16:03.184
Yeah.

16:03.269 --> 16:07.022
But right now I'm kind of
half-excited, half-worried.

16:07.106 --> 16:09.474
Well, there's no reason
to worry.

16:09.525 --> 16:11.693
Your mom's gonna be home
in no time.

16:11.777 --> 16:13.278
And, you know,
the best part

16:13.346 --> 16:14.896
about having
a little sister

16:14.981 --> 16:17.649
is if you do worry
and you do struggle,

16:17.700 --> 16:19.734
she's always there
for you --

16:19.819 --> 16:23.955
just like your mom's
always been there for me.

16:24.023 --> 16:28.359
♪ I need a woman
who believes in me ♪

16:28.411 --> 16:31.129
♪ I'll shine the way
through the darkest night ♪

16:31.196 --> 16:32.297
Hey.

16:32.364 --> 16:34.466
Wow.
Talk about a work of art.

16:34.533 --> 16:35.500
You look great.

16:35.551 --> 16:37.035
Thanks.

16:37.086 --> 16:39.370
So, you excited
for tonight?

16:39.422 --> 16:40.555
How do you feel?

16:40.640 --> 16:41.923
You know,
if there's a feeling

16:42.008 --> 16:43.224
of being
half totally excited

16:43.309 --> 16:44.676
and half completely ready
to panic,

16:44.727 --> 16:46.511
then that's how I feel.

16:46.562 --> 16:48.313
Oh, don't worry.
It's gonna be good.

16:48.380 --> 16:50.148
You're kind of great at the
picture-taking thing, you know.

16:50.215 --> 16:51.516
Thanks.

16:51.567 --> 16:53.351
Well, I'm glad
you think so.

16:53.402 --> 16:54.853
I wanted you to give this
to you.

16:54.904 --> 16:56.738
Oh. What is this?

16:56.822 --> 16:58.056
My way
of saying "thank you"

16:58.074 --> 16:59.407
for being there for me
this year.

16:59.492 --> 17:01.443
I couldn't have made it through
without my little sis.

17:01.527 --> 17:05.664
♪ ...Making all the right things
wrong ♪

17:05.731 --> 17:10.535
♪ as the days go by ♪

17:10.586 --> 17:12.170
I love it.

17:12.237 --> 17:13.872
I really do.

17:13.923 --> 17:15.589
I just want tonight to go well,
you know?

17:15.675 --> 17:17.709
For mom.

17:17.760 --> 17:20.962
Yeah. For mom.

17:21.047 --> 17:23.515
♪ ...By ♪

17:44.036 --> 17:47.489
Easy, son.

17:47.573 --> 17:49.908
You're okay.

17:49.959 --> 17:52.944
Can you hear me?

17:52.995 --> 17:54.796
Yeah.

17:54.864 --> 17:56.731
You collapsed
during the game.

17:56.799 --> 17:59.718
Nathan?

17:59.785 --> 18:01.836
How you feeling?

18:01.921 --> 18:04.055
I have to piss.

18:04.123 --> 18:06.925
You were
severely dehydrated.

18:06.992 --> 18:08.459
We have you
in these ice packs

18:08.511 --> 18:10.929
because your body temperature
was very high.

18:10.980 --> 18:13.932
Now, I need to ask you
some questions

18:13.983 --> 18:16.101
about the supplements
you're taking.

18:16.152 --> 18:18.370
Benzedrine?
Methedrine?

18:18.437 --> 18:20.105
Okay.

18:20.156 --> 18:23.408
What about speed,
cocaine, ecstasy?

18:23.475 --> 18:25.510
Hey, doc.
He's an athlete, not a junkie.

18:25.578 --> 18:27.278
He's also a kid.

18:27.346 --> 18:29.297
True.
But he's my kid.

18:29.365 --> 18:31.015
So, how about you play
a little more doctor

18:31.083 --> 18:32.484
and a little less
detective?

18:32.551 --> 18:35.270
Mr. Scott,
could I speak with you?

18:35.337 --> 18:39.941
♪ ...Storm slow us down ♪

18:40.009 --> 18:42.043
Listen to me, son.

18:42.128 --> 18:44.379
You're gonna be fine.
Okay?

18:44.447 --> 18:46.247
You've been hitting it
a little hard lately.

18:46.315 --> 18:48.600
We'll pull back a notch or two.
You'll be as good as new.

18:50.436 --> 18:52.053
Hell, the scouts
won't even remember this

18:52.121 --> 18:53.271
come the post-season.

18:56.759 --> 19:00.328
Hey, it's me.

19:00.396 --> 19:03.198
Uh...I guess
I'm just worried about you.

19:03.282 --> 19:07.035
I really hate
the way we ended things.

19:07.119 --> 19:07.902
So do I.

19:09.989 --> 19:13.491
Nobody answered the door.

19:13.542 --> 19:15.593
They're gone
for the weekend.

19:18.697 --> 19:21.216
How are you?

19:21.300 --> 19:23.685
Not so good.

19:23.753 --> 19:25.587
♪ ...Run us down ♪

19:25.671 --> 19:28.372
Tonight...

19:28.424 --> 19:29.591
I just need to...
Yeah.

19:33.729 --> 19:35.713
I've made
a lot of mistakes, Haley.

19:35.765 --> 19:37.849
♪ Run us down ♪

19:40.352 --> 19:41.569
Sometimes
because of my dad.

19:43.656 --> 19:46.524
Sometimes by choice.

19:51.363 --> 19:54.398
♪ Run us down ♪

19:54.450 --> 19:56.751
I just can't do it anymore.

19:56.836 --> 19:59.287
It's okay.

19:59.371 --> 20:00.205
No.

20:02.741 --> 20:05.076
When I fell to the floor
tonight...

20:07.246 --> 20:09.747
...I was so scared.

20:09.799 --> 20:12.016
I was so terrified.

20:15.604 --> 20:19.808
Then I saw you.

20:19.892 --> 20:23.611
And I promised myself
that if I could just get up,

20:23.696 --> 20:27.431
I would walk
straight over to you,

20:27.483 --> 20:31.035
and I would tell you
how much I need you...

20:32.938 --> 20:36.607
...How much I want you.

20:36.659 --> 20:40.044
Nothing else matters.

20:40.112 --> 20:46.301
♪ Please don't leave quite yet ♪

20:46.385 --> 20:51.055
♪ don't leave ♪

20:51.123 --> 20:53.624
♪ don't leave ♪

20:56.896 --> 20:59.597
Haley...

21:01.767 --> 21:06.154
♪ Please don't leave quite yet ♪

21:11.911 --> 21:14.112
Brooke, I need to tell you
something.

21:14.163 --> 21:16.698
I never told
my parents.

21:16.782 --> 21:18.166
Really?

21:18.250 --> 21:22.036
My ex-boyfriend's sister
drove me here.

21:22.121 --> 21:25.707
How did you hide it
from them?

21:25.791 --> 21:28.760
Well, I stayed in school
for the summer session,

21:28.827 --> 21:30.962
and then I took a semester
overseas.

21:32.848 --> 21:34.632
I just knew it was something
that my mom

21:34.683 --> 21:37.518
would hold against me
for the rest of my life.

21:37.603 --> 21:39.354
You know how moms are.

21:39.438 --> 21:42.390
I know how my mom is.

21:42.474 --> 21:46.644
♪ Licking sugar
from a razor blade ♪

21:46.695 --> 21:47.862
♪ pull the needle
from a hand grenade ♪

21:47.947 --> 21:48.947
You going somewhere?

21:49.014 --> 21:51.282
Ah.

21:51.350 --> 21:52.850
Back to New York.

21:52.902 --> 21:55.853
The designs
are excellent.

21:55.905 --> 21:59.457
The new line
should stabilize the company.

21:59.524 --> 22:02.877
There's nothing left
for me to do here.

22:02.962 --> 22:04.362
♪ ...I need ♪

22:04.413 --> 22:07.799
There <i>are</i> a few things
that I need to leave you with.

22:07.866 --> 22:09.384
We need to call
our publicist

22:09.468 --> 22:11.886
and arrange
a series of interviews

22:11.971 --> 22:14.222
announcing your return
to the company.

22:14.306 --> 22:15.673
You need to speak
with the people at Red

22:15.724 --> 22:17.541
and organize some sort of
charitable contribution,

22:17.593 --> 22:19.427
and you need to fly
to Los Angeles

22:19.511 --> 22:21.312
and tell that boy
that you love him.

22:21.380 --> 22:23.431
What?

22:23.515 --> 22:27.885
♪ There's no room to walk away ♪

22:27.937 --> 22:31.773
When I was young,
there was a boy who loved me.

22:31.857 --> 22:34.392
And I loved him back.

22:34.443 --> 22:36.377
But he wasn't
from my circle of friends,

22:36.445 --> 22:39.664
and he was different
than what my parents expected,

22:39.731 --> 22:41.616
so I let him go.

22:44.420 --> 22:48.890
And not a day has gone by
that I don't regret it.

22:48.958 --> 22:52.543
Why haven't you ever
told me this?

22:52.594 --> 22:55.096
Because I've been
a terrible mother.

22:55.180 --> 22:57.765
I have a daughter

22:57.850 --> 23:02.854
who is strong and bright,

23:02.921 --> 23:08.092
kindhearted, so beautiful,

23:08.160 --> 23:09.477
and I've nearly broken her

23:09.561 --> 23:12.530
with my inability
to open my heart.

23:12.597 --> 23:15.383
But I haven't broken her.

23:15.451 --> 23:18.436
She's just as strong
and beautiful

23:18.487 --> 23:20.605
and kindhearted as ever.

23:20.673 --> 23:23.825
Because if this boy Julian
loves you

23:23.909 --> 23:27.495
and you love him,

23:27.579 --> 23:31.049
that's all that matters.

23:31.116 --> 23:34.135
That is
the most important thing,

23:34.219 --> 23:36.421
and the clothes can wait.

23:38.674 --> 23:41.225
♪ Close enough to feel you ♪

23:41.293 --> 23:42.894
This is for you.

23:42.961 --> 23:45.763
♪ There's no room to walk away ♪

23:45.814 --> 23:47.648
What is it?

23:47.733 --> 23:49.984
It's the company.

23:50.069 --> 23:53.905
It's all yours --
100%.

23:53.972 --> 23:57.475
But why?

23:57.526 --> 24:02.080
I'd rather have my daughter
than a company.

24:02.147 --> 24:05.033
But you loved
this company.

24:05.100 --> 24:06.701
Yeah.

24:06.785 --> 24:09.871
And I was wrong.

24:09.955 --> 24:14.409
I should have loved you more
and the company less.

24:14.476 --> 24:18.162
♪ I'm on fire, love ♪

24:18.213 --> 24:22.266
I just didn't know how.

24:22.334 --> 24:27.188
♪ I'm on fire, love ♪

24:27.272 --> 24:30.108
I know my mom loves me.

24:30.175 --> 24:33.728
But we were distant for
a long time when I was young,

24:33.812 --> 24:36.864
and that was really hard.

24:36.949 --> 24:39.333
I never felt like
I knew her.

24:39.401 --> 24:42.937
I promise you,
I'm gonna know this child,

24:43.005 --> 24:46.290
and they'll know me...

24:46.358 --> 24:48.209
No matter what.

24:48.293 --> 24:54.215
♪ I'm on fire, love ♪

24:58.932 --> 25:00.667
<i>There was a woman in Texas,</i>

25:00.670 --> 25:03.221
<i>who gave birth to eight babies</i>
<i>all at once.</i>

25:03.289 --> 25:07.092
<i>Well, actually,</i>
<i>she gave birth to two,</i>

25:07.143 --> 25:10.445
<i>and then a couple weeks later,</i>
<i>she had six more.</i>

25:10.563 --> 25:12.347
<i>I don't really know</i>
<i>how that works,</i>

25:12.432 --> 25:16.318
<i>but it's not something you</i>
<i>forget once you hear about it.</i>

25:16.402 --> 25:18.820
<i>I just want my mom</i>
<i>to have one...</i>

25:18.905 --> 25:21.606
<i>And for both of them</i>
<i>to be okay.</i>

25:21.674 --> 25:24.493
♪ ...We've waged ♪

25:24.610 --> 25:29.314
♪ take us down a little ways ♪

25:29.365 --> 25:34.119
♪ got to let go ♪

25:34.170 --> 25:38.957
♪ got to let go ♪

25:39.008 --> 25:40.492
♪ got to let go ♪

25:40.543 --> 25:42.527
Hey, dad.
Everything okay?

25:42.595 --> 25:44.329
Yeah.

25:44.380 --> 25:47.299
♪ Seize the day ♪

25:49.719 --> 25:52.387
You know, when your mom got hurt
before you were born,

25:52.472 --> 25:54.339
I sat here.

25:54.390 --> 25:56.841
I prayed
that she'd be okay.

25:56.893 --> 25:58.643
And you, too.

25:58.694 --> 26:01.980
Did you cry?

26:02.031 --> 26:06.067
Yeah. I cried.

26:15.211 --> 26:18.463
I know I did a horrible thing,
okay?

26:20.800 --> 26:24.386
But I deserve to be punished
for that, not Haley.

26:24.470 --> 26:26.588
She's a good person.

26:26.672 --> 26:29.007
She'd be a great mother if...

26:34.564 --> 26:36.014
Look, I know it must suck

26:36.065 --> 26:37.816
how people are always asking
for things

26:37.883 --> 26:40.986
and never giving anything back.

26:41.053 --> 26:45.273
And I know that Keith saved me
at the bridge,

26:45.358 --> 26:50.745
but Haley saved me
long before the accident.

26:50.830 --> 26:53.782
There has to be
a miracle left for her.

26:53.866 --> 26:55.250
Please.

26:57.537 --> 27:00.589
Please.

27:00.673 --> 27:02.841
Don't take her from me.

27:04.844 --> 27:07.429
Don't take our child from her.

27:11.250 --> 27:14.019
Hi.

27:16.105 --> 27:17.889
Hi.

27:41.998 --> 27:44.332
Crazy, isn't it?

27:44.417 --> 27:46.668
Having a kid.
Yeah.

27:46.752 --> 27:49.638
I got to tell you, I'm
a little freaked out right now.

27:49.705 --> 27:54.226
I don't think
I'm ready for all...This.

27:54.293 --> 27:57.962
That's why they invented
mothers.

27:58.014 --> 28:00.232
You think our parents
felt like this?

28:00.299 --> 28:02.817
That they just wanted us
to have it better than them?

28:02.885 --> 28:07.339
To be better than them?

28:07.406 --> 28:09.641
Not to be them?

28:09.692 --> 28:12.627
I think if they did,

28:12.695 --> 28:15.413
then they were ready
to be parents.

28:15.481 --> 28:18.149
And if you do,
then you are, too.

28:18.200 --> 28:21.653
"Every child
comes with the message

28:21.704 --> 28:24.122
that God is not yet
discouraged of us."

28:29.895 --> 28:37.519
♪ You only know
what I want you to ♪

28:41.724 --> 28:48.513
♪ I know everything
you don't want me to ♪

28:48.564 --> 28:50.949
Hey, handsome.

28:51.017 --> 28:53.551
My whole family was here.

28:53.619 --> 28:57.355
It's usually best to be
in a coma for that,

28:57.406 --> 28:59.708
so nice work.

29:02.194 --> 29:03.395
I also need you
to tell you

29:03.462 --> 29:05.030
that it's gonna take longer

29:05.097 --> 29:07.449
to get into Nathan's
basketball games next year

29:07.516 --> 29:09.184
because my right boob

29:09.251 --> 29:12.754
is gonna set off
the metal detector.

29:12.838 --> 29:15.039
Apparently I still have
the bullet in me,

29:15.091 --> 29:19.027
so you can cross that off
your fantasy-girl wish list.

29:19.095 --> 29:22.981
So just between us,

29:23.048 --> 29:27.319
everybody's putting on
a really brave face,

29:27.386 --> 29:30.188
but I think
they're all really scared...

29:30.239 --> 29:33.024
Because they can't imagine
losing you.

29:33.092 --> 29:35.727
But that's not gonna happen,
is it?

29:38.414 --> 29:41.533
My man is too strong
for that.

29:41.584 --> 29:46.371
So, why don't you
surprise us all

29:46.422 --> 29:49.507
and open
those beautiful blue eyes

29:49.575 --> 29:52.260
and take my breath away...

29:52.328 --> 29:54.295
Like you know you do.

29:54.363 --> 29:56.381
Just open those eyes

29:56.449 --> 30:00.969
that see me
like no eyes ever have.

30:01.053 --> 30:03.972
♪ Your hands can bruise ♪

30:04.056 --> 30:05.807
And I'll be
right here waiting.

30:10.279 --> 30:22.407
♪ I don't have a choice,
but I still choose you ♪

30:22.458 --> 30:24.459
♪ oh ♪

30:24.543 --> 30:25.710
Hey.

30:25.778 --> 30:28.413
Nate says
they're getting close.

30:28.464 --> 30:29.547
You okay?

30:29.615 --> 30:30.615
Yeah.

30:32.385 --> 30:33.918
I'm just feeling thankful.

30:33.969 --> 30:38.390
For you and Haley
and my soon-to-be niece.

30:38.457 --> 30:39.957
It's exciting.

30:40.009 --> 30:42.677
Yeah.

30:42.762 --> 30:45.897
You know, we'll have kids
of our own someday.

30:45.964 --> 30:48.516
Well, they will have
your big, bushy eyebrows.

30:48.601 --> 30:51.135
Oh. And your adept
card-game abilities.

30:52.638 --> 30:53.938
You know,
you're not allowed

30:53.989 --> 30:56.157
to say we'll have a family
someday unless you mean it.

30:56.242 --> 30:58.093
Of course I mean it.

30:58.160 --> 31:00.111
I love you, you goof.

31:00.162 --> 31:02.247
Well, that's good...

31:02.314 --> 31:03.748
Because I love you, too.

31:03.816 --> 31:08.036
♪ But I always will ♪

31:08.120 --> 31:10.655
♪ I don't love you ♪

31:10.706 --> 31:14.826
♪ but I always will ♪

31:14.894 --> 31:16.094
It's really good
that you have Julian.

31:16.162 --> 31:17.295
You guys seem really happy
together.

31:17.363 --> 31:18.797
We are.
He's amazing.

31:18.848 --> 31:21.182
Yeah. I-it's be good
that there's two of you.

31:21.267 --> 31:24.001
I just couldn't do it alone,
you know?

31:24.053 --> 31:25.186
Raise a child.
I know.

31:25.271 --> 31:26.688
Oh!
Contraction.

31:26.772 --> 31:28.473
Okay.
Just breathe.

31:28.524 --> 31:30.191
You're doing great, Chloe.
No, I need drugs.

31:30.276 --> 31:31.359
You can do this.
Come on.

31:31.444 --> 31:32.610
Just breathe.

31:32.678 --> 31:34.195
Okay.
Okay.

31:34.280 --> 31:35.730
Okay. That's it.
Okay.

31:35.815 --> 31:37.816
You're doing great.

31:37.867 --> 31:41.870
You're gonna be
a good mom, Brooke.

31:43.622 --> 31:45.540
I just couldn't
do it alone.

31:45.624 --> 31:47.575
♪ I always will ♪

31:47.660 --> 31:49.694
I know.

31:49.745 --> 31:52.297
It's okay.

31:58.593 --> 32:00.751
<i>I guess out of everyone</i>
<i>who's ever been born</i>

32:01.480 --> 32:06.585
<i>probably the most famous birth</i>
<i>ever is Jesus.</i>

32:06.652 --> 32:10.839
<i>But people make a big deal</i>
<i>out of Pandas, too.</i>

32:13.960 --> 32:15.944
We need a name.

32:16.012 --> 32:18.547
Our baby's gonna be born
without a name.

32:20.817 --> 32:22.267
Oops.

32:23.853 --> 32:25.520
Okay, calm down.
It's okay.

32:25.605 --> 32:27.772
My dad once told me
about this baseball player

32:27.840 --> 32:29.558
named U.L. Washington,

32:29.642 --> 32:32.844
and the U.L.
stood for "un listed."

32:32.895 --> 32:37.115
We are not naming our baby

32:37.182 --> 32:38.900
"un listed."

32:38.985 --> 32:41.286
Okay. I have a name.

32:41.353 --> 32:42.654
Clear your head.
You ready?

32:42.705 --> 32:45.574
Uh-huh.
If it's a girl, Brooke.

32:45.658 --> 32:48.192
And if it's a boy...

32:48.244 --> 32:49.628
Brooke.

32:49.695 --> 32:53.465
If it's a boy, Julian.

32:53.532 --> 32:55.800
And if it's a girl...

32:55.868 --> 32:57.802
Julian.

32:57.870 --> 33:00.305
No. You can't name
a girl "Julian."

33:00.372 --> 33:01.840
Why not?

33:01.891 --> 33:04.542
We can name our baby
whatever we want.

33:07.146 --> 33:08.063
Mm.

33:08.147 --> 33:10.815
Mm.

33:10.883 --> 33:13.835
Mom's middle name
is Bob?

33:13.903 --> 33:15.237
Mm-hmm.
Wait.

33:15.304 --> 33:17.239
Haley's middle name is Bob?
Yeah.

33:17.323 --> 33:18.990
How does that happen?

33:19.058 --> 33:21.726
You know my dad's name
was James James, right?

33:21.794 --> 33:24.228
You make a good point.
But Bob?

33:24.280 --> 33:26.031
Is that short for Robert?

33:26.098 --> 33:27.249
No.
It's just Bob.

33:28.434 --> 33:29.668
How come?

33:29.735 --> 33:32.520
Well, before grandma and
grandpa ever had kids,

33:32.588 --> 33:33.788
they had a tabby cat.

33:33.856 --> 33:37.292
And they loved that cat
and took him everywhere.

33:37.376 --> 33:40.228
And his name was...
Bob?

33:40.296 --> 33:43.081
I was gonna guess Bob, too.
Ah. Then you're both right.

33:43.132 --> 33:44.549
Bob the cat.

33:44.600 --> 33:47.185
Oh.
He was their pride and joy.

33:47.252 --> 33:49.420
But he was
stubborn and tough,

33:49.472 --> 33:51.940
and he didn't really like
to be held.

33:52.024 --> 33:53.858
Anyway,
when Haley was born,

33:53.926 --> 33:55.193
she kept squirming
and squirming,

33:55.261 --> 33:57.128
and the doctors handed her
to grandma.

33:57.196 --> 33:59.314
And grandma was like,
"she keeps fighting me.

33:59.398 --> 34:02.000
She's tough and stubborn,
just like Bob."

34:02.068 --> 34:05.270
And so they named her
Haley Bob.

34:05.338 --> 34:07.973
Mom was named
after a cat.

34:08.040 --> 34:10.958
After a beautiful, tough,
old tabby cat.

34:11.043 --> 34:12.610
That's awesome.

34:12.661 --> 34:14.612
But mom's
not that tough.

34:14.664 --> 34:17.415
Ooh. Gonna have to disagree
with you on that one, buddy.

34:17.466 --> 34:19.217
Yeah.
Your mom's really tough.

34:19.284 --> 34:21.719
Do you know her and Aunt Taylor
used to totally go at it?

34:21.786 --> 34:22.887
Really? Like how?

34:24.590 --> 34:26.391
It's not funny, Taylor.
Ow!

34:26.458 --> 34:29.226
Let go!

34:29.295 --> 34:30.795
Whoa.

34:30.862 --> 34:32.013
Yeah.
That's not all.

34:32.098 --> 34:33.815
Remember when Chuck
was bullying you?

34:36.319 --> 34:38.103
Excuse me.
Can I talk to you for a second?

34:38.154 --> 34:39.971
I'm Haley Scott.
I'm Jamie's mom.

34:40.022 --> 34:41.438
Uh-huh.

34:41.489 --> 34:43.775
Jamie came home from school
upset the other day.

34:43.826 --> 34:45.577
I guess your son
was teasing him.

34:45.643 --> 34:47.829
Jamie?
Is he the one with the cape?

34:47.913 --> 34:49.331
Wow.

34:49.415 --> 34:52.117
5 is a little old for a cape,
don't you think?

34:52.168 --> 34:56.036
Maybe you should do him a favor,
take it away from him,

34:56.121 --> 34:57.756
and then he won't get teased
anymore --

34:57.823 --> 34:59.591
about the cape, anyway.

34:59.658 --> 35:01.993
Listen, honey,
if your little brat

35:02.044 --> 35:03.345
doesn't stop picking on
my son,

35:03.429 --> 35:05.496
not only will I give Jamie
permission to kick his ass,

35:05.548 --> 35:07.599
but I'll be kicking your ass
right alongside of him.

35:07.666 --> 35:11.136
Got that, bitch?
I'd like to see you try, little girl.

35:11.187 --> 35:13.054
Aah!

35:13.139 --> 35:16.007
Man.
Mom's kind of crazy.

35:16.075 --> 35:18.342
Yeah. I haven't even told you
about the slapping.

35:18.394 --> 35:19.811
There's slapping?

35:19.862 --> 35:22.063
Oh, there's slapping.
Hey, Brooke.

35:22.131 --> 35:23.782
Name a few people
that Haley's slapped.

35:23.849 --> 35:25.349
Jamie wants to warn
Lydia.

35:25.401 --> 35:29.788
Oh.
Well, there's Rachel...

35:31.907 --> 35:33.792
♪ I'm your kind of girl ♪

35:33.859 --> 35:35.326
...Renee...

35:39.665 --> 35:43.868
Ooh.
And Nanny Carrie.

35:44.703 --> 35:47.205
You get the hell out of my house
right now!

35:48.808 --> 35:52.811
Yeah. And in mom's defense,
nanny Carrie had that coming.

35:52.878 --> 35:53.762
Oh, yeah.

35:53.846 --> 35:55.814
Now that I think about it,

35:55.881 --> 35:57.982
you don't want to mess
with mom.

35:58.050 --> 36:00.685
Hey, Clay,
did mom ever attack you?

36:00.736 --> 36:04.222
Yeah.
But it was with her words.

36:04.273 --> 36:06.691
You know full well this lying
whore didn't sleep with Nathan,

36:06.742 --> 36:08.610
and you want to pay her
$200,000?

36:08.694 --> 36:10.412
Whoa.
I don't want to.

36:10.496 --> 36:12.197
I simply suggested
that it was an option.

36:12.248 --> 36:14.115
It's not an option, Clay.

36:14.200 --> 36:15.617
And while we're
suggesting things,

36:15.701 --> 36:17.502
let me suggest
that you are a huge reason

36:17.569 --> 36:19.637
why this is happening right now.
Okay.

36:19.705 --> 36:21.122
You love it --
the parties, the women.

36:21.207 --> 36:22.740
And you love having Nathan
alongside you

36:22.792 --> 36:23.758
more than anything else.

36:23.843 --> 36:24.909
That's not fair.

36:24.960 --> 36:26.428
No?
The picture?

36:26.512 --> 36:29.264
The one of that woman
draped all over my husband.

36:29.348 --> 36:31.382
What party was that at,
Clay?

36:31.434 --> 36:33.218
Who threw that party?

36:33.269 --> 36:35.186
I'm not saying
you don't love him

36:35.254 --> 36:36.688
because I know you do.

36:36.755 --> 36:39.641
But you love having him at your
side more than anything else.

36:39.708 --> 36:42.277
You could have protected him
from this.

36:42.361 --> 36:44.279
How, Haley?
He's a grown man.

36:44.363 --> 36:46.114
So are you.

36:46.198 --> 36:48.933
Start acting like it.

36:48.984 --> 36:50.768
Ooh.

36:50.820 --> 36:52.770
Yeah, you may --
you ought to tell Lydia

36:52.822 --> 36:56.124
just to never suggest
optional compromises.

36:56.192 --> 36:57.408
You should write that down.

37:02.798 --> 37:04.249
That's it, Chloe.
You're doing great.

37:04.300 --> 37:06.468
Now I need you to push, okay?
Here we go.

37:06.552 --> 37:07.886
And push.

37:07.953 --> 37:09.620
Push, Chloe.
Come on.

37:09.672 --> 37:11.289
Push.

37:11.340 --> 37:12.290
That's it.

37:12.341 --> 37:13.341
You're doing great, Chloe.

37:13.425 --> 37:14.342
Five counts.
Come on.

37:14.426 --> 37:16.144
1...2...

37:16.228 --> 37:19.814
3...4...5.

37:19.899 --> 37:21.465
Good job, Chloe.
You're doing great,

37:21.517 --> 37:23.234
and again.

37:23.302 --> 37:25.019
Push, Chloe, push.

37:25.104 --> 37:26.454
Come on.

37:29.024 --> 37:31.142
Hey, it's you.

37:31.193 --> 37:34.145
Oh. Hey.

37:34.196 --> 37:35.947
Brooke, this is...

37:35.998 --> 37:37.682
Eric. Hi.

37:37.750 --> 37:39.284
Hi.

37:39.335 --> 37:40.869
What are you
doing here?

37:40.953 --> 37:43.004
I was about to ask you
the same thing.

37:43.088 --> 37:45.623
That's
my girlfriend, Chloe.

37:48.010 --> 37:50.494
I'm about to be
a father.

37:57.911 --> 38:00.324
<i>I think people love babies</i>
<i>because they see stuff</i>

38:00.454 --> 38:02.539
<i>like hopes and dreams</i>
<i>in their eyes.</i>

38:02.623 --> 38:05.191
<i>They see the future,</i>
<i>and they see goodness</i>

38:05.243 --> 38:07.911
<i>and the chance they have</i>
<i>to be better than us.</i>

38:08.028 --> 38:10.964
<i>So I think</i>
<i>babies are pretty cool.</i>

38:11.031 --> 38:13.750
<i>Oh, and baby rabbits</i>
<i>are even cooler...</i>

38:13.834 --> 38:16.086
<i>Although I'm kind of glad</i>
<i>Chester is a boy</i>

38:16.170 --> 38:17.637
<i>and never had babies</i>

38:17.705 --> 38:19.539
<i>'cause I'm not sure</i>
<i>I'd be able to give them up.</i>

38:19.590 --> 38:21.874
<i>I'd be too worried</i>
<i>that they'd be okay</i>

38:21.926 --> 38:24.678
<i>and that someone would love</i>
<i>them as much as I would.</i>

38:24.745 --> 38:31.484
♪ If ever I do hurt you ♪

38:31.552 --> 38:39.326
♪ make your willows bend ♪

38:39.393 --> 38:45.382
♪ if ever I deceive you ♪

38:47.602 --> 38:52.372
♪ darling,
do not hang your head ♪

38:54.909 --> 39:02.682
♪ if ever I betray you ♪

39:02.750 --> 39:08.188
♪ cast shadows on your light ♪

39:11.058 --> 39:15.362
♪ I pray
that you may pardon ♪

39:17.632 --> 39:19.932
She just changed her mind,
Brooke.

39:19.984 --> 39:21.985
She didn't want
to do it alone,

39:22.069 --> 39:25.271
and then she wasn't alone.

39:25.323 --> 39:28.742
She held her in her arms,

39:28.793 --> 39:30.961
and she just couldn't
go through with it.

39:33.881 --> 39:38.301
It was a girl?

39:40.588 --> 39:42.789
Yeah.

39:49.847 --> 39:51.014
It's a girl.

39:51.098 --> 39:52.299
Yay!

39:52.366 --> 39:55.435
Yes!

39:55.503 --> 39:56.903
Whoo!

39:56.971 --> 40:02.325
♪ We are but failed attempts ♪

40:05.029 --> 40:07.030
Oh. What do you say,
buddy?

40:07.114 --> 40:08.665
Is mom all right?
And the baby?

40:08.749 --> 40:10.200
Yeah, yeah.
Everyone's fine.

40:10.284 --> 40:11.251
When can we see her?

40:11.318 --> 40:12.318
Well...

40:13.371 --> 40:14.204
Brooke.

40:17.425 --> 40:18.541
You okay?

40:18.626 --> 40:20.159
Yeah.

40:20.211 --> 40:22.879
I'm just so happy
for you guys.

40:22.963 --> 40:28.968
♪ ...Greatest triumphs ♪

40:29.020 --> 40:32.639
♪ we cannot shake the fear ♪

40:36.143 --> 40:40.146
♪ that the ones
that we most treasure ♪

40:40.197 --> 40:41.514
Hi.

40:41.565 --> 40:43.867
Hi.

40:43.951 --> 40:47.787
Lydia, I want you to meet
someone

40:47.855 --> 40:51.041
you're gonna love
so much.

40:51.125 --> 40:52.659
This is
your Aunt Brooke.

40:52.710 --> 40:56.746
Brooke, this is
Lydia Bob Scott.

40:58.666 --> 41:00.050
You want to hold her?

41:00.134 --> 41:02.802
Yeah.

41:02.870 --> 41:05.204
♪ ...Deserve you ♪

41:05.256 --> 41:07.340
Oh.

41:07.391 --> 41:10.593
♪ But if I ever dare forget ♪

41:10.678 --> 41:14.347
<i>353,015.</i>

41:14.398 --> 41:17.984
<i>That's how many babies</i>
<i>were born today.</i>

41:18.051 --> 41:21.404
<i>And this one is mine.</i>

41:23.574 --> 41:25.608
<i>Every child</i>
<i>comes with the message</i>

41:25.693 --> 41:30.196
<i>that God is not yet discouraged</i>
<i>of us.</i>

41:30.247 --> 41:34.501
♪ Again ♪

